Title:
Stop Being Weird: CET, Call Stack Spoofing Detections, and “Normal” Execution Flows (MassDriver)

Type:
Blog Post

Short Summary (4–8 sentences max):
- The post analyzes modern Windows call stack spoofing (gadget-based synthetic frames) and why it increasingly fails against Elastic’s behavioral detections and Intel CET shadow stack enforcement.  
- It explains Elastic rules that flag “image_rop” behavior (returns not preceded by a `call`) and signatureable call stack summaries caused by rare “call-preceded” ROP gadgets.  
- With CET, classic spoofing breaks because modifying return addresses desynchronizes the normal stack from the shadow stack, causing faults.  
- The proposed workaround is to stop spoofing and instead proxy sensitive/monitored API calls from shellcode to a “normal” on-disk artifact thread via `PostThreadMessage`, yielding clean, legitimate call stacks.  
- For sleep masking, it uses a CET-friendly fiber-based sleep routine (switching to a fiber that calls `Sleep` and returns), avoiding the “sleeping beacon” wait-stack pattern.  
- Useful for red teams/pentesters and implant developers adapting to CET + call-stack-based EDR detections; also useful for defenders to understand emerging evasion patterns and where to add telemetry.

Technical Focus:
- Elastic call stack spoofing detections (“image_rop”, gadget patterns, call stack summary signatures)
- Intel CET / shadow stack implications for ROP and stack tampering
- API-call proxying from shellcode to a benign thread (message-based RPC)
- Windows fibers for CET-compatible stack switching and sleep obfuscation
- Gadget hunting constraints (call-preceded gadgets) and signatureability

Use Cases:
- Implement CET-compatible alternatives to gadget-based call stack spoofing
- Reduce EDR call-stack anomalies by moving monitored API calls into “normal” module execution
- Build loaders/implants that proxy high-risk APIs (e.g., `LoadLibraryA`, memory APIs) through a broker thread
- Sleep masking using fiber switching to avoid suspicious wait/sleep call stacks
- Defensive research: create detections for message-based API brokers and fiber-based sleep patterns

Keywords:
CET, shadow stack, Control-flow Enforcement Technology, call stack spoofing, stack spoofing detection, Elastic EDR, image_rop, ROP gadget, jmp reg gadget, synthetic frames, RtlUserThreadStart, BaseThreadInitThunk, PostThreadMessageA, WM_USER, worker thread, fibers, ConvertThreadToFiber, CreateFiber, SwitchToFiber, LoadLibraryA, Sleep, Beacon, BOF, GadgetHunter